    "body": "Always pass LC_ALL=C to diff when parsing its output.\n\nCloses #38838\n\nSigned-off-by: Tomas Slusny <slusnucky@gmail.com>\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-07T17:02:12Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Cannot rly add test for this if other locales arent enabled on the system in locale.gen, not sure if there are but this is test that i used locally after enabling german locale:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n  it('works with non-English locale', function()\r\n    -- Clear Neovim with German locale\r\n    clear({ env = { LC_ALL = 'de_DE.UTF-8', LANG = 'de_DE.UTF-8' } })\r\n    command('packadd nvim.difftool')\r\n    \r\n    command(('DiffTool %s %s'):format(testdir_left, testdir_right))\r\n    local qflist = fn.getqflist()\r\n\r\n    -- Should detect differences regardless of locale\r\n    assert(#qflist > 0, 'difftool should detect differences with non-English locale')\r\n\r\n    local entries = {}\r\n    for _, item in ipairs(qflist) do\r\n      table.insert(entries, { text = item.text, rel = item.user_data and item.user_data.rel })\r\n    end\r\n\r\n    -- Should show the same entries as with English locale\r\n    eq({\r\n      { text = 'M', rel = 'file1.txt' },\r\n      { text = 'D', rel = 'file2.txt' },\r\n      { text = 'A', rel = 'file3.txt' },\r\n    }, entries)\r\n  end)\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo enable locale just go to etc/locale.gen and uncomment whatever and then run `locale-gen`",
            "created_at": "2026-04-07T11:24:42Z",
